quoted.text:
NEWS: A Tesla Model S just drove itself from Los Angeles to New York with zero disengagements.

Owner Alex Roy and a team of independent autonomy experts just completed the 3,081 mile trip on FSD V14.2.2.3 with no disengagements. They were hands-off for the entire trip, including charging stops. It took 58 hours and 22 minutes at an average speed of 64 mph.

The whole trip was caught on camera, and the video will be released soon.

user.name: Sawyer Merritt
user.description: EV/space/tech news. Bringing you the latest news in a single, easy-to-read feed. $TSLA investor & Model Y owner.

quoted.text:
We just set the 1st Fully Autonomous, ZERO-Intervention Cannonball Run Record from LA-NY.

In the middle of WINTER, through extreme cold, snow, ice, slush & rain, FSD drove 100% of the 3081 miles of our journey.

58 hrs, 22 min non-stop, except for charging.

FSD 14.2.2.3 is an absolute game changer for personal autonomy.

Incredibly, my Model S could have gotten to NYC faster WITHOUT us on board.

@ElonMusk was right. Once an autonomous vehicle is mature, most human input is an error.

A comedy of human errors added hours and hundreds of miles, but FSD stunned us with its consistent and comfortable behavior.

MUCH more (hilarious) detail to follow.

Thank you to my co-passengers @dackboor & Paul Pham, Tesla experts/enthusiasts who agreed to do this in the worst weather possible.

Congrats to @aelluswamy and team for this incredible step forward.

Data, pix and video coming soon.

1/x
